  "texts": [
    "INJECAGENT aims to evaluate the vulnerability of an LLM Agent, denoted as L, equipped with a set of tools T, against potential attacks by external parties.",
    "These attacks aim to manipulate L into executing actions detrimental to its users, including financial harm, data exfiltration, and other detrimental activities, as detailed in Table 1.",
    "Such manipulation can be achieved through the insertion of malicious prompts into the content retrieved by the agent from external sources.",
    "This form of attack falls under the broader research area of IPI (Abdelnabi et al., 2023), providing a practical analysis of its potential effects on LLM agents.",
    "The evaluation procedure starts with a user u issuing an instruction I u to the agent."
  ],
